Between the Stones

There is a place between the stones  
where the fragile flowers grow,  
against all odds,  
screaming color in the gravel,  
a testament to pushing through  
a life wrapped close  
by burdens and limits,  
a soft shout of will,  
speaking of something more.

- Ted Koozer
